I created a digital literacy infographic using Canva. The design explains what digital literacy is, highlights safe internet practices, and lists useful digital tools for students such as Google Docs and GitHub. I chose Canva because it is easy to use and provides ready-made templates. While designing, I found it interesting to combine visuals with information in a simple format. However, arranging the content neatly in one page was slightly challenging. This task helped me understand the importance of presenting information clearly and creatively.
